# Structure of C# 🏗️

```csharp
using System; // Import standard library

namespace HelloWorld {
    class Program {
        static void Main(string[] args) {
            Console.WriteLine("Hello World!");
        }
    }
}
```
- `using System`: Gives access to `Console`.
- `Main`: The entry point.
- `Console.WriteLine`: Prints newline.

# Storing Data 📦

C# is strongly typed.

```csharp
int age = 25;
double price = 19.99;
char grade = 'A';
string message = "Hello";
bool isFun = true;
```

## The `var` Keyword
Let compiler guess the type (Type Inference).
```csharp
var x = 10; // x is int
```

# Fancy Strings ✨

The easiest way to format strings is using the `$` symbol.

```csharp
string name = "Alice";
int age = 30;

// Old way
Console.WriteLine("Name: " + name + ", Age: " + age);

// New way (Interpolation)
Console.WriteLine($"Name: {name}, Age: {age}");
```

# Changing Shapes 🔄

Input is always string, so we need to convert it.

```csharp
Console.Write("Enter age: ");
string input = Console.ReadLine();

// Method 1: Convert Class
int age = Convert.ToInt32(input);

// Method 2: Parse
int age2 = int.Parse(input);
```

